metadata.name: BRUMALIA XVII ρ [ρώ] Reginos
metadata.description:
Brumalia, whose ritual became 'imperial', provided the opportunity to celebrate the capital and the emperor, as well as the promoter of the feast. Through the organisation of receptions, banquets, dances, mimes, games and gifts, the sovereign demonstrated his power and magnificence before his subjects.
